data.mission: Create a single script/Make target that runs scaffold generation and asserts presence/content of required files (REPORT_OUTLINE.md, CASE_STUDY_TEMPLATE, QA reports), failing fast and writing results into /outputs/qa/.

Draft runtime/outputs/QA_GATE.md with numbered checks mapped to required files/fields (verbatim claim, source/context, provenance anchor) and wire it into the QA runner so failures block generation of QA_REPORT outputs.

Run the tooling in the target environment and save a timestamped console transcript plus any validator outputs into /outputs/qa/ (or runtime/outputs/qa/) to establish a reproducible baseline and identify failure points (paths, missing deps, permissions).

Implement a single command that (a) runs the QA gate against DRAFT_REPORT_v0.md + pilot artifacts, then (b) emits QA_REPORT.json and QA_REPORT.md with per-check status, error messages, and remediation pointers.

Define v1 schema (fields + required/optional + enums for workstream type), then implement a minimal CLI (e.g., `python -m case_studies.add`) that creates a new case folder with a prefilled metadata file and runs schema validation before allowing commit.
